In Win32, there are 512 fopen files limit(can be set up to 2048).

AssetsManagerEx::batchDownload() create network::DownloadTaskCURL classes as many as their download-file-list in the network::DownloadTaskCURL::init().

It seems the logic must move to DownloadTaskCURL::writeDataProc() or DownloadTaskCURL::initProc();

When using textDefinition (or embedded solutions like the UIRichText) it doesn't make possible to set the shadow Color;

line 518 of CCLabelTTF.js
// shadow
        if (textDefinition.shadowEnabled)
            this.enableShadow(textDefinition.shadowOffsetX,
                textDefinition.shadowOffsetY,
                textDefinition.shadowOpacity,
                textDefinition.shadowBlur);

If changing it to
// shadow
        if (textDefinition.shadowEnabled)
            this.enableShadow( textDefinition.shadowColor, //needs to be added.
                cc.size(textDefinition.shadowOffsetX, textDefinition.shadowOffsetY),
                textDefinition.shadowBlur);

It would be possible to do it.
